      {
        "id": "ed800beb4b313e87d4e2ec033804ae8c8188529f",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 93,
          "name": "Vijay Venkatesh Kumar",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "vijayv81@gmail.com",
          "username": "vv770d"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-09-28 02:36:24.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\n(2 comments)\n\nPath for DH and PH need to be updated. Alex - this update is more to distribute the cert in heat based solution. Are there any consul config update required to support TLS for both DH and PH?",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "954cd94377e8fa60b19657d35826ab5fa68057da",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1949,
          "name": "Alex Shatov",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "ashatov@hotmail.com",
          "username": "alex_sh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-09-28 13:15:40.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\nVijay is correct \n\n- we need to provide the same path to cert_directory as in k8s blueprints\ndeployment-handler:\n  cert_directory: '/opt/app/dh/etc/cert/'\n\npolicy-handler:\n  cert_directory: '/opt/app/policy_handler/etc/tls/certs/'\n\n- plus we need to change the consul-kv record for the policy-handler to have the proper url with \"https\" and hostname instead of ip-address !\nblueprints/input-templates/phinputs.yaml:\n    policy_engine :\n        url : \"http://{{ policy_ip_addr }}:8081\"  <<<--- will not work without hostname + need https\n\n    deploy_handler :\n        url : \"http://deployment-handler:8188\"  <<<--- need https",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
